reviews.review_text:
Crazy in Woostah! This show had a couple of great memories for me.  By now I was getting used to the weirdness of not traveling to see a Dead show...just had to go downtown!  I had people crashing my pad - I got off my job at 5:00 and still made the show ontime with no problem! No parking hassles, no getting lost cuz ur too stoned on the highway... instead of going to see the Dead, the boys came to us!  Worcester!
 Anyhow, the other cool thing was that due to Worcester connections, I had a backstage pass.  Nice to wear that badge around your neck - but I had to admit, I felt a little detached from the crowd.  Roving with no real 'seat' was weird.  But I did get to meet some hussy by the side of the stage (Bobby's gal for Worcester?)  And gave a nod and good night to JG on the way out as he hopped in his limo.  Weird,Worcester -
As for the show, nothing startling, but the Crazy Fingers in the 2nd - any song from BfA is fine by me.  but the jamming was a little weird throught...only one song 10 min +.  Crazy, crazy night...

Wooster... Yeah this was an out of control weird scene. The show was weird because their was a major conversion of college/boarding school kids swarming to get into the show "sold out." Scalpers everywhere and acid abounding. I didn't get into the show but listened to a simulcast on the radio with other fellow New Hampshire prep school friends in a gnarly parking lot drinking crappy beer and smoking mexican weed which was worth it's weight in gold at the time. Awesome experience in the shakedown area. Dead 101
